## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of family in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Family is the bounded continuity structure
through which kinship,
care,
shared belonging,
domestic relation,
and inherited continuity
become meaningful.

Family is not merely a relationship label.
It is the governed relation group
that persists across time
and affects life, housing, inheritance, and social belonging.

## architectural_position
Family sits between:
- life continuity
- relationship continuity
- housing/co-residence
- care and responsibility
- inheritance and historical continuity

## required_behavior
- family identity must remain explicit
- family membership basis must remain explicit
- current and historical family states must remain distinguishable
- care/responsibility meaning must remain explicit
- family relation must not collapse into generic relation

## canonical_rules
- family membership does not imply unlimited authority
- historical family trace must remain queryable
- family and generic relationship semantics must remain distinguishable
- ambiguous family membership or authority fails closed

## state_model
The family domain distinguishes:
- proposed family relation
- active family state
- changed family state
- restricted family state
- historical family state
- closed family state

## actor_boundary
- family member
- guardian/caregiver
- reviewer
- operator
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if family membership basis is unclear, stop authority-sensitive action
- if care/responsibility scope is unclear, fail closed
- if family becomes historical, preserve continuity trace
- if relation changes, preserve prior family history

## review_checklist
- family identity is explicit
- membership model is explicit
- care/responsibility meaning is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
